summary: SummaryLancôme Advanced Génifique Night Cream repairs the skin's moisture barrier overnight and instantly locks in hydration lasting for 72 hours*. Night after night, skin feels stronger and looks healthier. *In a clinical study on 24 women, after 72 hours
details: DetailsBenefitsAdvanced Génifique Night cream repairs the skin's moisture barrier while you sleep. A stong skin barrier helps to lock in hydration and defend against external aggressors.The formula works to restore hydration and plumpness while you sleep to wake up with skin looking radiant and well-rested.Over time, this anti-aging cream reduces the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, to leave skin looking youthful and feeling healthy.The formula transforms to soften and melt into the skin as you apply it, instantly soothing and hydrating the skin.Key Ingredients10% Bifidus Prebiotic: Known to support a favorable environment for good bacteria that is present on the skin's surface.Triple Ceramide Complex: Ceramides are lipids naturally found in the skin barrier and are crucial in restoring and replenishing the skin's moisture barrier.Hyaluronic Acid: A naturally occurring molecule that is found throughout the skin, known for its ability to enhance moisture retention and skin hydration.Formulated with 94% natural origin ingredients.*Formulated without mineral oil, parabens, Phenoxyethanol, & Dimethicone. Non-comedogenic & suitable for sensitive skin types.*Lancôme considers ingredients to be natural origin if it is unchanged from its natural state or has undergone processing yet still retains more than 50% of its molecular structure from its original natural source.Research ResultsCLINICALLY MEASURED RESULTS (after 8 weeks of use):Smoothness improved by +43%Radiance improved by +37%Firmness improved by +35%Plumpness improved by +33%Evenness improved by +23%Fine Lines reduced by -21%Item 2601561How To UseBefore going to bed, cleanse face and neck, thoroughly removing all makeup.If applying serums, first apply Génifique Serum and then any other serums in your night skincare routine.Finally, apply an even layer of Génifique Night cream to skin nightly.IngredientsOleamido-1,3-Octadecanediol, Adenosine, Mannose, Coco-Caprylate/Caprate, Ascorbyl Glucoside, Hydroxyacetophenone, Hydroxypalmitoyl Sphinganine Hydroxypropyl Starch Phosphate, Capryloyl Salicylic Acid, Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Lactic Acid, Lactobacillus, Acetic Acid, Maltodextrin, Faex Extract / Yeast Extract / Extrait De Levure, Polyglycerin-3, Polyglyceryl-3 Beeswax, Cetyl Alcohol, Tocopherol, Sodium Benzoate, Linalool, Limonene, Citronellol, Parfum / Fragrance, (F.I.L. T294734/1).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: Before going to bed, cleanse face and neck, thoroughly removing all makeup.If applying serums, first apply Génifique Serum and then any other serums in your night skincare routine.Finally, apply an even layer of Génifique Night cream to skin nightly.

reviews.headline: Lancome Genifique
reviews.comments: Lovely product, too expensive

reviews.headline: Sensitive skin BEWARE!!!
reviews.comments: This literally gave me a very bad chemical burn. I recieved this and tried it  a few years ago when ulta was giving a sample for your birthday month. I can still tell where i had the burn, years later. Truly awful. It did make me learn to not just put anything on my face.

reviews.headline: Not hydrating enough for mature skin
reviews.comments: I am half way through the jar and this night moisturizer is just not hydrating enough on its own.  I am a former oily/combo complexion that gradually  switched to dry/combo throughout my 40's and this may work well for the < 40 group.  I prob would have liked it during my oily days but definitely not enough moisture for me now.

reviews.headline: Smells like bug spray
reviews.comments: I am not pleased with this purchase. The cream smells like bug spray and is not moisturizing enough.  My skin is not hydrated  in the morning after using this. Do not recommend, too expensive for what it is.

reviews.headline: Love
reviews.comments: I first originally got this product as a birthday sample and I absolutely loved it. Was so happy when I finally for my hands on them in full size. It is verg hydrating on the skin keeps my skin very moist as I have extremely dry skin. I often put it on during night time as part of my night time skin routine. Every morning I still feel my skin very smooth I would not suggest this product with anyone with oilly skin at all.

reviews.headline: It did not moisturize my skin!
reviews.comments: This cream by appearance looked very rich, but a few minutes after I applied, my face felt dry! It peeled with other skincare and the scent to me was awful. It reminds me more of a sculpting cream more than a moisturizer. Will not repurchase.

reviews.headline: love love love
reviews.comments: I have super dry skin and I love this produst!! must try!

reviews.headline: Great except smell
reviews.comments: Ugh- i couldnt place the smell at first, but i think it has tobacco undertones. I like the cream but will not repurchase just on the smell alone.

reviews.headline: Makes skin feel softer
reviews.comments: I use with Lacome serum, makes my face feel softer

reviews.headline: Lancôme is that girl
reviews.comments: I love this cream. Im 30 y/o with sensitive acne prone oily skin. This does not clog my pores or break me out at all. It has a slight scent but nothing overpowering. My skin LOVES this paired with the genifique serum. So impressed by the quality of lancome.

reviews.headline: Smells like Windex
reviews.comments: The consistency of the cream is fine but the smell is terrible. It smells like Windex. I mixed up the container a few times thinking maybe something had settled and needed to be mixed back in. Did not help. The results are  what I would expect of any basic night cream,  nothing overwhelming.   I love Lancome's other products, this one just isn't for me.

reviews.headline: Gets rid of my acne!!
reviews.comments: I have dry acne prone skin and struggle to find something the moisturizes deeply but doesnt break me out. Ive tried so many products but this one works the best. Literally OVERNIGHT I can tell a difference with my breakouts and how hydrated my skin is. I hate how pricey it is, but justify it by telling myself a dermatologist appt would cost $100 :)

reviews.headline: Meh and breakouts
reviews.comments: The only thing I noticed about this cream was that it made me break out. Aside from that, I didn't notice any improvements in my skin. I just can't justify this product at such a high price point. I expected more.

reviews.headline: Pricey but so good
reviews.comments: Bought during 21 days of beauty sale. Oh my gosh I'll have to use it sparingly because of how expensive it is. Full price would be crazy. I love it so much i just might.

reviews.headline: Good moisturizer bad smell
reviews.comments: OK this moisturizer is amazing for not clogging your pores, hydrating your face, and great for sensitive skin! All around I have used everything from Le Mer, Dermalogica, Estee Lauter, etc. you name it I've tried it! However, it smells like straight up windex… so, that is my only thing. I would check it out before you buy it so you can understand the smell. That is why I give it a three.

reviews.headline: This is worth the money
reviews.comments: I got this as a sample and I was hoping I wouldnt like it. Unfortunately this night cream is amazing. Overnight results. I woke up with smooth soft skin and my makeup went on so nice the next day. Looks like I'm going to need to splurge when my sample runs out.

reviews.headline: Amazing
reviews.comments: Love how this makes my skin feel

reviews.headline: Love this cream!
reviews.comments: Smells like baby lotion and works wonders! I can tell a huge difference right away and my skin is glowing!

reviews.headline: Birthday Sample
reviews.comments: The beat night cream I've ever used. A little goes a long way. I've had the little sample for 2 months at still have half a left. Can't wait to buy the full size

reviews.headline: This is a keeper!
reviews.comments: The Lancôme Advanced Génifique Night Cream gets a A+! I have used the product for just over 7 days. I saw a difference on day 1 and every day after. I love the way this night cream has revitalized my neck area. my neck area is soft and supple. I was concerned that I would experience drying and other reactions but I have not had any bad results. I would not hesitate to recommend this product to my friends.

faceoff_positive.headline: Worth every penny

faceoff_negative.comments:
I used Lancome Advanced Genifique Repairing Night Cream for about 3 weeks before writing this review.
A few things to note:
*I am dark skinned
*I am African
*I have sensitive skin
*I have oily skin

So if you fall in those categories maybe this review will work for you.
After using this for weeks, I didn't see that much of a difference on my face. Or at least, not a difference that I would applaud. I had a few pimples that I didn't have before. My skin did not get better and not necessarily worse because the pimples weren't huge enough to be visible but I could feel the bumps when I applied it or washed my face.
Additionally, I did have one pimple below my eye but I'm not sure if that was from the cream, but just in case it was, it might be information a person needs to know before purchasing this product.
Prior to my use of Lancome Advanced Genifique Repairing Night Cream, my face was clear, no acne, no wrinkles no scars and I feel like it's still fairly the same aside from the aforementioned tiny pimples (bumps) on my jaw line and above my brows.

Maybe if you had problems on your face like wrinkles this would work, but I wouldn't recommend it for someone with no issues.
faceoff_negative.headline: No visible "recommendable" change
